  <name>Linux Network Speed Indicator</name>
  <summary>Top-bar and tray network speed monitor for Linux desktops</summary>
  <developer id="io.github.masummsnr">
    <name>Masum</name>
  </developer>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">linux-network-speed-indicator.desktop</launchable>
  <provides>
    <binary>linux-network-speed-indicator</binary>
  </provides>
  <description>
    <p>Linux Network Speed Indicator is a lightweight network speed monitor for Ubuntu GNOME, Debian GNOME, and other Linux desktops that support AppIndicator or StatusNotifier items.</p>
    <p>It shows live download and upload throughput in the top bar or tray, supports automatic or fixed units, allows split or single-direction display modes, and can start automatically on login.</p>
  </description>
